TITLE:: AtkFoa
summary:: A class that stores some global FOA variables for the Ambisonic Toolkit
categories:: Libraries>Ambisonic Toolkit>ATK Platform & Configuration
related:: Classes/Atk, Classes/AtkHoa, Guides/ATK-Glossary

DESCRIPTION::
The AtkFoa class defines variables that may be used to integrate FOA and HOA workflows within the ATK library.


CLASSMETHODS::

PRIVATE:: initClass


SUBSECTION:: Ambisonic order

METHOD:: defaultOrder
Ambisonic order, FOA.

code::
AtkFoa.defaultOrder
::


SUBSECTION:: Component ordering & normalisation


METHOD:: format
Designation indicating ambisonic emphasis::component ordering:: and emphasis::component normalisation::. The Ambisonic Toolkit FOA convention is FuMa-FuMa, i.e., Furse-Malham (FuMa), Gerzon / Furse-Malham (MaxN).

code::
AtkFoa.format
::


METHOD:: ordering
Ambisonic Toolkit FOA ambisonic emphasis::component ordering:: convention: Furse-Malham (FuMa). See link::https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ambisonic_data_exchange_formats#Component_ordering#ordering::.

code::
AtkFoa.ordering
::


METHOD:: normalisation
Ambisonic Toolkit ambisonic emphasis::component normalisation:: convention: Gerzon / Furse-Malham (MaxN). See link::https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ambisonic_data_exchange_formats#Normalisation#normalisation::.

code::
AtkFoa.normalisation
::


SUBSECTION:: Radial & NFE


METHOD:: refRadius
Ambisonic Toolkit FOA emphasis::reference radius::, in meters.

code::
AtkFoa.refRadius
::


METHOD:: speedOfSound
Ambisonic Toolkit (FOA) speed of sound, in meters per second.

code::
AtkFoa.speedOfSound
::


METHOD:: setSpeedOfSound
Setter for link::#*speedOfSound::.

note::
Setting this value only effects the speed of sound for soundfield analysis via link::Classes/FoaNF::, and does NOT currently update the value used by link::Classes/FoaProximity:: & link::Classes/FoaNFC::.
::


ARGUMENT:: mps
Speed of sound, in meters per second.



